#   - Rust pulldown-cmark: fastest, lowest memory, hard to extend
#   - Go goldmark:         medium speed, AST-flexible, easy
#                           to extend via Extender
#   - Node markdown-it:    fastest pure-JS, flexible via rule
#                           pipeline, MASSIVE plugin ecosystem
#
# All three are CommonMark 0.30/0.31 compliant; they differ in
# their intermediate representation (events vs AST vs token
# array) and extension model (Options bitflags vs Extender
